  "suggestion": "[affective-neuroscience+polyvagal-theory+dynamical-systems+clinical-psychology] IMPLEMENT NOW — Polyvagal Gate: Autonomic Pre-Filter. Before active inference runs, compute autonomic state from (arousal × threat-type × history-depth): SAFE (arousal<0.4, no threat) → full need-space active; MOBILIZED (arousal 0.4–0.75 OR threat stimulus) → safety/esteem/fairness only, precision×2; SHUTDOWN (arousal>0.75 AND history≥2 chronic stressors) → collapse all needs to safety, precision×5, behavior forced to withdrawal/freeze. This gates which attractors are reachable — no deep esteem attractor can fire during SHUTDOWN. Adds 1 function (~30 lines) before computeFreeEnergy; replaces the ad-hoc `person.arousal > 0.75` psychopathology heuristic with a principled physiological prior. Three states map to Porges' three circuits: ventral vagal / sympathetic / dorsal vagal. — Math: autonomicState = argmax{ SAFE: σ(−arousal), MOBILIZED: σ(arousal − 0.4) × threatFlag, SHUTDOWN: σ(arousal − 0.75) × historyDepth }; precision_need *= stateMultiplier[autonomicState][need]; [cognitive-psychology+linguistics+narrative-identity+attribution-theory] IMPLEMENT NOW — Narrative Role Parser: Situation → Story Grammar → Role Vector. Every psychological situation has implicit narrative structure (Mandler & Johnson 1977; Propp morphology). Parse stimulus.description + context into 4 role slots: [protagonist_locus, antagonist_present, goal_clarity, obstacle_type]. protagonist_locus ∈ {self, other, system} — determines internal vs. external attribution (locus-of-control). obstacle_type ∈ {physical, social, internal, informational} — determines coping strategy. goal_clarity ∈ [0,1] from novelty inversion. Cross-pollinate: use formal grammar patterns (regex over the description field) to assign roles, then map role-vector to a behavior bias that *adjusts* the attractor landscape pull before free energy is computed. 4 patterns cover ~70% of benchmarks. — Math: roleVector = parse(stimulus.description); attractorBias[i] += dot(roleVector, ATTRACTOR_ROLE_WEIGHTS[i]); winner = argmin_i((dist² − attractorBias[i]) / depth_i); [personality-psychology+dynamical-systems+Big-Five+computational-psychiatry] REFINEMENT — Trait-Gated Attractor Reachability. Current attractors have fixed baseDepth; traits modulate precision but not which attractors are reachable. Proposal: Big Five traits act as *reachability gates* on the attractor landscape — high neuroticism makes negative attractors (fear, shame, rumination) reachable from smaller stimuli (lower threshold); high agreeableness blocks aggression attractor; high conscientiousness makes avoidance attractor harder to enter. Implement as: threshold_i = baseThreshold / traitGate(traits, attractor_i.name). Attractor only competes if |X_final − A_i| < threshold_i. This unifies personality theory with dynamical systems — traits ARE landscape topology, not just precision weights. Adds ~20 lines to the attractor winner selection loop. — Math: threshold_i(traits) = base_i × exp(−traitAffinity(traits, attractor_i)); attractor_i eligible iff dist_i < threshold_i; winner = argmin eligible (dist_i² / depth_i)",
